      <akn:section eId="sec_3_1204_05">
        <akn:num>3-1204.05</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Officers; meetings; quorum.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_3-1204_05_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>From among the members of each board and advisory committee, the Mayor shall designate a chairperson.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_3-1204_05_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Each board and advisory committee shall determine the times and places of its meetings and shall publish notice of regular meetings at least 1 week in advance in the District of Columbia Register.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_3-1204_05_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A majority of the appointed members of each board and advisory committee shall constitute a quorum.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_3-1204_05_d">
      <akn:num>(d)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>An affirmative vote of a majority of a quorum shall be required to approve a measure before a board.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
